<item>
            <title>[LU-13567] LNet: For Multi-Rail setup set arp kernel parameters</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13567</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For Multi-Rail setups there are a few parameters which need to be set properly to allow for proper ARP resolution. It&apos;ll be best to set these parameters from LNet to avoid having the user run into unexpected behavior&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
net.ipv4.conf.all.rp_filter=0
net.ipv4.conf.ib0.accept_local=1
net.ipv4.conf.ib0.arp_ignore=1
net.ipv4.conf.ib0.arp_filter=0
net.ipv4.conf.ib0.arp_announce=2
net.ipv4.conf.ib0.rp_filter=0 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
